The paper deals with the performance guarantees of local search and greedy algorithms for scheduling, which are topics in the fields of algorithms and optimization (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), network economics (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The abstract mentions worst-case lower bounds and smoothed analysis, which are common concepts in algorithms and optimization research. The paper also discusses the price of anarchy in routing games, which is a topic in game theory and network economics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.GT, and cs.LG, followed by cs.NE and cs.AI.
